1: What is TaskUs.
TaskUs is a publicly traded outsourcing and digital services company that helps other businesses manage customer support, content moderation, AI-related operations, trust and safety services, back-office processes, and other business functions. It was founded in 2008 by Bryce Maddock and Jaspar Weir and is headquartered in New Braunfels, Texas.

You can learn more on the company's official website: TaskUs

What does TaskUs do?

TaskUs provides services such as:

Customer experience (CX) and customer support
Content moderation and trust & safety operations
AI data services, including data annotation and model support
Back-office and business process outsourcing (BPO)
Sales and customer acquisition support
Digital operations and consulting services
